Why dual-license?

The engine is Apache 2.0 so anyone can build on the core truth library —
integrate verifiable receipts, agent memory, deployment orchestration,
and on-chain anchoring into any product, commercial or otherwise.

The gateway-lite API server is AGPL-3.0 to ensure that improvements to
the network-facing service are shared back with the community. If you
run a modified Lucid gateway as a service, your users deserve access to
those improvements.

This is the same pattern used by MongoDB (SSPL), Grafana (AGPL),
and other infrastructure projects that balance open collaboration with
sustainable development.

